\begin{tikzpicture} \begin{axis}[ axis x line = bottom, axis y line = middle, every axis y label/.style={at={(ticklabel cs:1.1)}}, y label style={at={(axis description cs:0,1.15)},anchor=north}, ylabel = {$p(g)$}, every axis x label/.style= {at ={(ticklabel cs:1)}}, x label style={at={(axis description cs:1.1,0)},anchor=east}, xlabel = {$g$}, xmin = 0, xmax = 1, ymin = 0, ymax = 3, ] \addplot[thick, smooth, domain = 0:3] {4.37*x}; \end{axis} \end{tikzpicture}

example.statement:
Are both of these graphs functions? Why or why not?
The image on the left is the graph of the curve \cos x on the interval [0,2\pi].
\begin{tikzpicture} \begin{axis}[ axis x line = middle, axis y line = middle, every axis y label/.style={at={(ticklabel cs:1.1)}}, y label style={at={(axis description cs:0,1.1)},anchor=north}, ylabel = {$y$}, every axis x label/.style= {at ={(ticklabel cs:1)}}, x label style={at={(axis description cs:1.1,.48)},anchor=east}, xlabel = {$x$}, trig format plots = rad, xmin = 0, xmax = 6.5, ymin = -1.5, ymax = 1.5, ] \addplot[thick, smooth, domain = 0:2*pi] {cos(x)}; \end{axis} \end{tikzpicture}
The image on the right is the graph of the curve whose x-coordinate is given by the rule x^3-3x, and whose y-coordinate is given by the rule 3x^2-9.
\begin{tikzpicture} \begin{axis}[ axis x line = middle, axis y line = middle, every axis y label/.style={at={(ticklabel cs:1.1)}}, y label style={at={(axis description cs:.5,1.1)},anchor=north}, ylabel = {$y$}, every axis x label/.style= {at ={(ticklabel cs:1)}}, x label style={at={(axis description cs:1.1,.65)},anchor=east}, xlabel = {$x$}, xmin=-4.5,xmax=4.5, ymin=-9.5,ymax=4.5, xtick = {-4,-2,2,4}, ytick = {-8,-6,-4,-2,2,4}, ] \addplot[domain=-3:3,samples=50]({x^3-3*x},{3*x^2-9}); \end{axis} \end{tikzpicture}

Find the domain of the functions below:



		f(x) = \dfrac{3x^4 - 5}{x^2 +2x - 8}




		g(k) = \sqrt[3]{1-7k}




		h(t) = \sqrt{2-t} - \sqrt{3+t}

Without referring to the vertical line test, explain why the graph below is not a function.


		The image on the right is the graph of the curve whose x-coordinate is given by the rule x^2-3, and whose y-coordinate is given by the rule x^3-3x.



			\begin{tikzpicture}
				\begin{axis}[
						axis x line = middle,
						axis y line = middle,
						every axis y label/.style={at={(ticklabel cs:1.1)}},
						y label style={at={(axis description cs:.5,1.1)},anchor=north},
						ylabel = {$y$},
						every axis x label/.style= {at ={(ticklabel cs:1)}},
						x label style={at={(axis description cs:1.1,0)},anchor=east},
						xlabel = {$x$},
						xmin=-5, xmax = 5,
						ytick = {-8,-6,-4,-2,2,4},
					]
					\addplot[domain=-5:0,samples=50] {-1*x};
					\addplot[domain=0:5,samples=50] {x}; 
				 \end{axis}
			\end{tikzpicture}

A function h is defined by h(x) = \begin{cases}3-x \amp x \lt 2\\ x^2+x \amp x \geq 2 \end{cases}



		Evaluate h(-2), h(3), and h(2).



		Sketch the graph of h

image.latex-image:

\begin{tikzpicture}
	\begin{axis}[
		axis x line = middle,
		axis y line = middle,
		every axis y label/.style={at={(ticklabel cs:1.1)}},
		y label style={at={(axis description cs:.5,1.1)},anchor=north},
		ylabel = {$y$},
		every axis x label/.style= {at ={(ticklabel cs:1)}},
		x label style={at={(axis description cs:1.1,.65)},anchor=east},
		xlabel = {$x$},
		xmin=-2,xmax=4,
		ymin=0,ymax=12
	]
		\addplot [domain=-2:2,samples=50] {3-x}; 
		\addplot [domain=2:3, samples=50] {x^2+x};
		\coordinate (circle1) at (2,1);
		\coordinate (circle2) at (2,6);
	\end{axis}
	\fill[white] (circle1) circle (.1);
	\draw (circle1) circle (.1);
	\fill (circle2) circle (.1);
\end{tikzpicture}

example.statement:
Identify the intervals for which the function is increasing and decreasing.
This is the graph of the function \dfrac{1}{3}x^3 - \dfrac{1}{2}x^2 - 2x on the interval [-3,4].
\begin{tikzpicture} \begin{axis}[ axis x line = middle, axis y line = middle, every axis y label/.style={at={(ticklabel cs:1.1)}}, y label style={at={(axis description cs:.4,1.1)},anchor=north}, ylabel = {$y$}, every axis x label/.style= {at ={(ticklabel cs:1)}}, x label style={at={(axis description cs:1.1,.6)},anchor=east}, xlabel = {$x$}, xmin=-3.5,xmax=5, xtick = {-3,-2,-1,1,2,3,4}, ] \addplot[thick,smooth,domain = -3:4] {(1/3)*x^3 -(1/2)*x^2 -2*x}; \end{axis} \end{tikzpicture}

image.latex-image:

\begin{tikzpicture}
	\begin{axis}[
	axis x line = middle,
		axis y line = middle,
		every axis y label/.style={at={(ticklabel cs:1.1)}},
	y label style={at={(axis description cs:.35,1.1)},anchor=north},
		ylabel = {$y$},
		every axis x label/.style= {at ={(ticklabel cs:1)}},
		x label style={at={(axis description cs:1.1,.2)},anchor=east},
		xlabel = {$x$},
	xmin=-2,xmax=4,
	]
		\coordinate (circle1) at (2,2);
		\coordinate (circle2) at (2,-1);
		\addplot[thick,smooth,domain = -2:2] {3-0.5*x};
		\addplot[thick,smooth,domain = 2:4] {2*x-5};
	\end{axis}
	\fill[white] (circle1) circle (.1);
	\draw (circle1) circle (.1);
	\fill (circle2) circle (.1);
\end{tikzpicture}


